'Man?'
'Many a doer of great deeds might say no more,'
'It has been guessed already,'
'Fare you well!'
'But what is a hobbit?'
'for there have been strange portents here of late. But pass on now quickly! For the Lord of Minas Tirith will be eager to see any that bear the latest tidings of his son, be he man or-'
'But you come with tidings of grief and danger, as is your wont, they say.'
'This is the last portion of the wall to be put in defence: the least open to attack, for it looks towards our friends of Rohan. Do you know aught of them? Will they answer the summons, think you?'
